图片来源：视觉中国记者：侯卓铠“ 英国成为欧洲地区首个呼吁国内汽车制造商转产医疗设备的国家。
2007-9-25 21: 48 "Britain became the first country in Europe to call for domestic car makers to switch to medical equipment.
”北京时间3月16日晚间，据路透社消息称，由于英国NHS（英国国家医疗服务体系）仅有5000余台呼吸器可供使用，政府当日已经与当地多家汽车制造商进行商讨，希望这些制造商能够帮助制造包括呼吸机在内的卫生设备。
The NHS, with just over 5,000 respirators available, was in talks with a number of local carmakers that day in an attempt to help make sanitary equipment, including breathing machines, Reuters reported on Monday.
其中福特、本田、劳斯莱斯等多家汽车公司已经收到相关政府工作人员的接洽。
Among them, Ford, Honda, Rolls-Royce and other auto companies have received relevant government staff contact.
唐宁街也表示：“传播冠状病毒爆发做准备是国家的当务之急，我们正在呼吁制造业以及所有具有相关专业知识的人，这些人可能能够团结起来，帮助国家应对这场国家危机。
"To prepare for the outbreak of this coronavirus is a national priority," Downing Street said. "We are calling on the manufacturing industry and all those with the relevant expertise who may be able to unite to help the country respond to this national crisis.
我们需要加快生产重要设备，例如呼吸器，我们需要企业来帮助我们，为这项全国努力提供帮助。
We need to speed up the production of vital equipment, such as respirators, and we need businesses to help us in this national effort.
”英国当地新冠肺炎疫情持续蔓延，根据英国卫生和劳动保障部当地时间每天下午两点左右公布当日最新疫情数据，截至16日，英国境内确诊者总数1543人，新增172例。
The latest figures, released at around 2 p.m. local time, showed a total of 1,543 confirmed cases and 172 new cases in the UK as of Sunday.
英国卫生部长马特·汉考克（Matt Hancock）也表示，由于预计病例的急剧增加，英国国内急需用以救治疾病的呼吸器。
Matt Hancock, Britain's health minister, also said the UK urgently needed breathing apparatus to treat the disease because of the expected sharp increase in the number of cases.
对此，英国首相鲍里斯·约翰逊（Boris Johnson）已经与英国国内多家汽车制造商展开对话，希望为国家卫生局（National Health Service）生产“基本医疗设备”的支持。
In response, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has held talks with a number of British carmakers in hopes of supporting the National Health Service in the production of "essential medical equipment."
目前，福特发言人证实英国政府等相关结构已经接洽了公司，并表示：“我们希望在可能的情况下提供帮助，目前正在讨论中。
A Ford spokesman confirmed that the British government and other relevant agencies had approached the company and said: "We would like to help if possible and are currently under discussion.
”据了解，福特在英国经营两家发动机工厂，分别位于威尔士南部小镇布里真德和伦敦东部达格南（Dagenham），2019年两家工厂产能约为110万。
Ford is understood to operate two engine plants in the UK, one in Brijende, south Wales, and the other in Dagenham, east of London, with a capacity of about 1.1 million in 2019.
不过早前据CNBC援引知情人士透露，福特汽车计划在今年9月关闭布里真德的工厂，从而实现全球业务重组。
But earlier, CNBC quoted people familiar with the matter as saying Ford plans to restructure its global operations by closing its plant in September.
本田也表示已经收到相关通知，正在与英国政府就转产呼吸器的可行性进行商讨。
Honda also said it had received notification and was in discussions with the British government on the feasibility of converting respirators.
本田汽车英国工厂位于英格兰西南部斯文敦，也是本田在欧盟地区仅有的一座工厂，主要生产思域车型2019年年产量近11万辆。
Honda Motor's UK plant in Swindon, southwest of England, is Honda's only plant in the EU, producing nearly 110,000 Civic models annually in 2019.
然而与福特汽车采取的措施相同，该工厂将在2021年正式关闭。
However, in line with Ford's approach, the plant will officially close by 2021.
另外，PSA旗下的沃克斯豪尔和劳斯莱斯也收到英国政府接洽。
In addition, PSA's Vauxhall and Rolls-Royce have also been approached by the British government.
丰田汽车也表示“非常乐意”向英国政府提供帮助。
Toyota also said it was "very happy" to help the British government.
目前，新冠肺炎疫情已经影响欧洲各大汽车企业的正常生产工作。
At present, the new crown pneumonia epidemic has affected the major European auto enterprises normal production work.
菲亚特克莱斯勒（FCA）已于3月11日宣布暂时关闭意大利本土的Pomigliano、Melfi、Atessa和Cassino四座工厂；法拉利、兰博基尼、玛莎拉蒂近几日也宣布暂时关闭工厂；大众集团旗下西雅特汽车也正在计划缩减位于西班牙巴塞罗那的Martorell工厂产量。
Fiat Chrysler announced on March 11 the temporary closure of four mainland plants, Pomigliano, Melfi, Atessa and Cassino; Ferrari, Lamborghini and Marsalatti have also announced temporary closures in recent days; and VW's Seattle vehicle is planning to scale back production at its Martorell plant in Barcelona, Spain.
欧洲汽车工业正在遭受几十年来最大的停产停工危机。
Europe's auto industry is suffering its biggest shutdown crisis in decades.
英国虽然成为欧洲地区首个呼吁国内汽车制造商转产医疗器械的国家，但外媒也表示目前尚不清楚汽车制造商如何转产专业医疗设备，需要哪些国际零件或需要哪些认证。
The U.K. became the first European country to call for domestic carmakers to switch to medical devices, but foreign media said it was unclear how carmakers would switch to specialized medical equipment, which international parts would be needed or which certifications would be needed.
